  "solution": [
    "## Solutions to Coordinate Geometry Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: Cartesian Coordinates",
    "",
    "**a)** General: ax² + bxy + cy² + dx + ey + f = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** Complete square: translate to center, rotate to eliminate xy term",
    "",
    "**c)** Vertices: extreme points, foci: points with constant sum/difference of distances",
    "",
    "**d)** e = c/a for ellipse, e = √(1 + b²/a²) for hyperbola",
    "",
    "**e)** Tangent: F(x,y) + F_x(x-x₀) + F_y(y-y₀) = 0",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: Polar Coordinates",
    "",
    "**a)** r = ed/(1 ± e cos θ) for conics with focus at pole",
    "",
    "**b)** Ellipse: r = a(1 - e²)/(1 + e cos θ)",
    "",
    "**c)** Hyperbola: r = a(e² - 1)/(1 + e cos θ)",
    "",
    "**d)** Parabola: r = 2p/(1 + cos θ)",
    "",
    "**e)** Directrix at θ = π/2, focus at origin",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: Parametric Equations",
    "",
    "**a)** Ellipse: x = a cos θ, y = b sin θ",
    "",
    "**b)** Hyperbola: x = a sec θ, y = b tan θ",
    "",
    "**c)** Parabola: x = 2at, y = at² (focus at origin)",
    "",
    "**d)** Rational: x = (1-t²)/(1+t²), y = 2t/(1+t²) for circle",
    "",
    "**e)** Trigonometric: use angle parameters for standard forms",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: Coordinate Transformations",
    "",
    "**a)** Translation: x' = x - h, y' = y - k",
    "",
    "**b)** Rotation: x' = x cos θ + y sin θ, y' = -x sin θ + y cos θ",
    "",
    "**c)** Affine: linear transformation followed by translation",
    "",
    "**d)** Invariants: discriminant, eccentricity, type of conic",
    "",
    "**e)** Transformation matrix preserves quadratic form structure",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: Affine Transformations",
    "",
    "**a)** Conic transforms as quadratic form under linear map",
    "",
    "**b)** New matrix A' = Mᵀ A M for transformation matrix M",
    "",
    "**c)** Ellipse remains ellipse, hyperbola remains hyperbola",
    "",
    "**d)** Affine invariants: type, position of center, axes ratio",
    "",
    "**e)** Classification preserved under affine group",
    "",
    "### Exercise 6: Projective Coordinates",
    "",
    "**a)** Homogeneous: ax² + bxy + cy² + dxz + eyz + fz² = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** Projective transformations: linear fractional transformations",
    "",
    "**c)** Cross ratio (z₁,z₂;z₃,z₄) = (z₁-z₃)(z₂-z₄)/(z₁-z₄)(z₂-z₃)",
    "",
    "**d)** Pascal's theorem, Brianchon's theorem",
    "",
    "**e)** Pole-polar duality: lines ↔ points",
    "",
    "### Exercise 7: Oblique Coordinates",
    "",
    "**a)** General: x = u cos α - v cos β, y = u sin α - v sin β",
    "",
    "**b)** Transformation: Jacobian matrix for coordinate change",
    "",
    "**c)** Metric tensor determines distances and angles",
    "",
    "**d)** Crystal systems: hexagonal, monoclinic coordinates",
    "",
    "**e)** Dot product: g_{ij} du^i du^j",
    "",
    "### Exercise 8: Curvilinear Coordinates",
    "",
    "**a)** Parabolic: u = √(x² + y² + z² + x), v = √(x² + y² + z² - x)",
    "",
    "**b)** Elliptic: confocal ellipses and hyperbolas",
    "",
    "**c)** Hyperbolic: coordinate surfaces are hyperboloids",
    "",
    "**d)** Orthogonal: coordinate lines perpendicular",
    "",
    "**e)** Laplace equation separates in these systems",
    "",
    "### Exercise 9: Complex Coordinates",
    "",
    "**a)** z = x + i y, conic as f(z, \\bar{z}) = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** Analytic functions, Cauchy-Riemann equations",
    "",
    "**c)** z(θ) = a cos θ + i b sin θ for ellipse",
    "",
    "**d)** Contour integration, residue theorem",
    "",
    "**e)** Branch cuts for multivalued functions",
    "",
    "### Exercise 10: Coordinate Systems in 3D",
    "",
    "**a)** Ellipsoid: x²/a² + y²/b² + z²/c² = 1",
    "",
    "**b)** Cylindrical: ρ²/a² + z²/c² = 1 for elliptic cylinder",
    "",
    "**c)** Spherical: sin²θ cos²φ/a² + sin²θ sin²φ/b² + cos²θ/c² = 1",
    "",
    "**d)** Hyperboloid: x²/a² + y²/b² - z²/c² = 1",
    "",
    "**e)** Intersection with coordinate surfaces gives conics",
    "",
    "### Exercise 11: Conformal Coordinates",
    "",
    "**a)** Möbius transformations preserve angles",
    "",
    "**b)** Local angle preservation property",
    "",
    "**c)** Complex potential w = f(z) for 2D fields",
    "",
    "**d)** Isothermal: equal temperature lines perpendicular to heat flow",
    "",
    "**e)** Harmonic functions satisfy Laplace's equation",
    "",
    "### Exercise 12: Coordinate Geometry Theorems",
    "",
    "**a)** Apollonius circle, Simson line, etc.",
    "",
    "**b)** Section formula: point dividing in ratio m:n",
    "",
    "**c)** Centroid: intersection of medians",
    "",
    "**d)** Distance: √((x₂-x₁)² + (y₂-y₁)²)",
    "",
    "**e)** Coordinate proofs using distance and section formulas",
    "",
    "### Exercise 13: Coordinate Transformations in Physics",
    "",
    "**a)** Galilean: x' = x - v t, t' = t",
    "",
    "**b)** Lorentz: x' = γ(x - v t), t' = γ(t - v x/c²)",
    "",
    "**c)** Light cone: x² + y² + z² - c² t² = 0",
    "",
    "**d)** Lagrangian coordinates in fluid mechanics",
    "",
    "**e)** Curvilinear coordinates in electromagnetism",
    "",
    "### Exercise 14: Computational Coordinate Systems",
    "",
    "**a)** Matrix multiplication for transformations",
    "",
    "**b)** Round-off errors in floating point arithmetic",
    "",
    "**c)** Homogeneous coordinates for 3D graphics",
    "",
    "**d)** Barycentric coordinates for triangles",
    "",
    "**e)** Quaternion representations for rotations",
    "",
    "### Exercise 15: Advanced Coordinate Methods",
    "",
    "**a)** Generalized coordinates in Lagrangian mechanics",
    "",
    "**b)** Riemannian coordinates on curved surfaces",
    "",
    "**c)** Clifford algebra for geometric algebra",
    "",
    "**d)** Tensor coordinates in differential geometry",
    "",
    "**e)** Fiber bundle coordinates in modern geometry"
  ],
